    nearbyAttractions: `
    <h4>Nearby Attractions</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Lekgalameetse Nature Reserve</strong><br>Lekgalameetse is an immense 18,718-ha mountain wilderness area of protected escarpment, scenic landscape, mountain vegetation, and wildlife. The place of water, this is where many of the prominent rivers of the Lowveld originate.<br>Phone: +27 15 293 3600</li>
      <li><strong>Kaross Workers</strong><br>Kaross embodies the essence of being African. Kaross brings creative hands together as well as the beauty and passion that goes into creating incredible hand-embroidered works of functional art. Kaross sells hand-embroidered African art and one-of-a-kind home décor items handmade by the VaTsonga people of South Africa.<br>Phone: +27 15 345 1458</li>
      <li><strong>Wegraakbosch Cheese Farm</strong><br>Experience highlights of the cheese-making process which is hand made over a fire in the original Swiss methods. All cheese tours require a booking.<br>Phone: +27 72 361 0664</li>
      <li><strong>Magoebaskloof Canopy Tours</strong><br>Go on a journey into a previously inaccessible realm of nature as you traverse the upper level of indigenous forest and ancient mountain cliffs overlooking the spectacular Groot Letaba River gorge. The tour includes awe-inspiring slides and platform viewpoints over three giant waterfalls, each tumbling up to 20 metres into the sparkling river below.<br>Phone: +27 83 866 1546</li>
      <li><strong>Debengeni Falls</strong><br>In the verdant beauty of the Magoebaskloof, which is in the splendour of the northern part of the Drakensberg Mountain Range, is Debengeni Falls. This waterfall is an idyllic example of the untouched, untainted appeal of Limpopo Province. The Ramadipha River tumbles 80 metres into the massive bowl of water at its base, demonstrating the unharnessed power of nature.<br>Phone: +27 13 754 2700</li>
      <li><strong>Kruger National Park</strong><br>Kruger National Park in northeastern South Africa is one of Africa’s largest game reserves. Its high density of wild animals includes the Big 5: lions, leopards, rhinos, elephants, and buffalos. Hundreds of other mammals make their home here, as do diverse bird species such as vultures, eagles, and storks. Mountains, bush plains, and tropical forests are all part of the landscape. Nearly 2 million hectares of unrivaled diversity of life forms fuses with historical and archaeological sights.Phone: <br>+27 13 735 4000</li>
      <li><strong>Panorama Pedals</strong><br>Are you a cyclist that enjoys exploring the great outdoors? Travel like you never have before. See sights through new eyes as we take you on an adventure you will never forget.<br>Phone: +27 82 362 0647</li>
      <li><strong>Ebenezer Dam</strong><br>Ebenezer Dam is an earth-fill type dam on the Groot Letaba River near Tzaneen, Limpopo, South Africa. The Broederstroom also flows into the dam. Ebenezer Dam is a popular and particularly pretty dam visited often by locals and visitors for picnics, camping, birding, fishing, and boating.<br>Phone: +27 15 276 2341</li>
      <li><strong>Agatha Crocodile Ranch</strong><br>Agatha Crocodile Ranch is a fantastic tourist attraction situated on a beautiful avocado farm in Tzaneen, Limpopo. Founded by Milan and Blanka Darazs in 1978 when Blanka gave her husband two baby crocodiles as a gift, Agatha Crocodile Ranch has grown into a world-class crocodile farm offering tours and exciting experiences to both local and international visitors alike.<br>Phone: +27 15 307 4398</li>
    </ul>
  `,
